<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="84" pageId="3" pageNumber="83" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,335,264,290]" box="[189,335,264,290]" pageId="3" pageNumber="83">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,335,264,290]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="83" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,335,264,290]" pageId="3" pageNumber="83">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,634,311,373]" box="[234,298,311,337]" pageId="3" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,298,311,337]" pageId="3" pageNumber="83">Male</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,634,311,373]" box="[189,634,346,373]" pageId="3" pageNumber="83">
MEASUREMENTS. Total length: 
<quantity box="[537,630,346,373]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6" pageId="3" pageNumber="83" unit="mm" value="3.6">3.6 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,1400,412,790]" pageId="3" pageNumber="83">
STRUCTURE. Metope with two large depressions besides of midline above postclypeus and with strong median carina running from upper margin to middle and with weaker sublateral carinae joined to metopial upper margin, but not fused to median carina, and running slightly beyond eyes (
<figureCitation box="[1294,1392,482,508]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[189,232,1962,1988]" captionTargetBox="[235,1359,1015,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-239@3.[216,1371,1000,1924]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Superciliaris anichkini sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ZIN), external view. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Frontal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761686" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761686/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="83">Figs 1C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[189,227,517,543]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[308,1258,279,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-12@8.[308,1279,265,1783]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 4. Superciliaris spp., external view (weak carinae and margins are indicated by dotted lines). A–C. S. anichkini sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ZIN). A. Half of face and left paranotal lobe, frontal view. B. Face, frontal view. C. Tegula and basal part of forewing, lateral view. D–E. S. celebensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH). D. Face, frontal view. E. Tegula and basal part of forewing, lateral view. F–G. S. tawaiensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH). F. Face, frontal view. G. Tegula and basal part of forewing, lateral view. Abbreviation: sc = sublateral carinae of metope. No to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761692" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761692/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="83">4B</figureCitation>
). Postclypeus not large, weakly swollen, smooth, without carinae. Metope and coryphe joined at acute angle in shape of short process (in lateral view) (
<figureCitation box="[831,922,552,579]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[189,232,1962,1988]" captionTargetBox="[235,1359,1015,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-239@3.[216,1371,1000,1924]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Superciliaris anichkini sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ZIN), external view. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Frontal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761686" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761686/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="83">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Coryphe wide, transverse, shagreened, with three large bulges (triangular medial one and two rounded lateral ones); anterior margin strongly convex; posterior margin widely concave; lateral margins and posterior margin keel-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[1291,1385,623,649]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[189,232,1962,1988]" captionTargetBox="[235,1359,1015,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-239@3.[216,1371,1000,1924]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Superciliaris anichkini sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ZIN), external view. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Frontal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761686" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761686/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="83">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Pronotum short, 0.5× as long as coryphe at midline, without carinae but with pair of small bulges besides of midline; anterior margin widely convex; posterior margin straight. Mesonotum 3 × as long as pronotum, with strong median carina and with pair of large bulges laterally. Each forewing with large bulge in claval basement (
<figureCitation box="[497,588,764,790]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[189,232,1962,1988]" captionTargetBox="[235,1359,1015,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-239@3.[216,1371,1000,1924]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Superciliaris anichkini sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ZIN), external view. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Frontal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761686" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761686/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="83">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Fore and middle femora not flattened. Hind legs missed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,1399,829,925]" pageId="3" pageNumber="83">
COLORATION (
<figureCitation box="[345,414,829,855]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[189,232,1962,1988]" captionTargetBox="[235,1359,1015,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-239@3.[216,1371,1000,1924]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Superciliaris anichkini sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ZIN), external view. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Frontal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761686" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761686/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="83">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). General coloration brown yellowish to dark brown. Eyes dark brown. Forewings with yellowish areas and whitish spots in cells except in basal third. Abdominal sternites, pygofer and styles dark brown. Anal tube light brown.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761686" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6761686" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761686/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="83" startId="3.[189,232,1962,1988]" targetBox="[235,1359,1015,1905]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,1398,1962,2024]" pageId="3" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,269,1962,1988]" pageId="3" pageNumber="83">Fig. 1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Gnezdilov, 2022" authorityName="Gnezdilov" authorityYear="2022" box="[281,553,1962,1988]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Superciliaris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anichkini" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[281,553,1962,1988]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="83">Superciliaris anichkini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[561,656,1963,1989]" pageId="3" pageNumber="83" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, ♂, holotype (ZIN), external view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1081,1102,1962,1988]" pageId="3" pageNumber="83">A</emphasis>
. Dorsal view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1281,1299,1962,1988]" pageId="3" pageNumber="83">B</emphasis>
. Lateral view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[259,280,1997,2023]" pageId="3" pageNumber="83">C</emphasis>
. Frontal view. Scale bar = 1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[188,1399,265,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="84">
MALE TERMINALIA (
<figureCitation box="[410,482,265,292]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[221,1339,427,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[189,1398,420,1852]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 5. Superciliaris anichkini sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ZIN), genitalia. A. Pygofer and anal tube, lateral view (basal part of penis showed by dotted line).B. Penis (aedeagus shaded) and connective, lateral view. C. Apical part of phallobase inflated in water. D. Penis, ventral view. E. Style, lateral view. F. Style, dorsal view. G. Anal tube, dorsal view. No to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761694" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761694/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="84">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Pygofer vertically elongate, with convex hind margins (
<figureCitation box="[1167,1263,265,292]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[221,1339,427,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[189,1398,420,1852]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 5. Superciliaris anichkini sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ZIN), genitalia. A. Pygofer and anal tube, lateral view (basal part of penis showed by dotted line).B. Penis (aedeagus shaded) and connective, lateral view. C. Apical part of phallobase inflated in water. D. Penis, ventral view. E. Style, lateral view. F. Style, dorsal view. G. Anal tube, dorsal view. No to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761694" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761694/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="84">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
). Anal tube wide and short, enlarged and truncate apically, with nearly straight posterior margin (in dorsal view) (
<figureCitation box="[198,298,335,362]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[221,1339,427,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[189,1398,420,1852]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 5. Superciliaris anichkini sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ZIN), genitalia. A. Pygofer and anal tube, lateral view (basal part of penis showed by dotted line).B. Penis (aedeagus shaded) and connective, lateral view. C. Apical part of phallobase inflated in water. D. Penis, ventral view. E. Style, lateral view. F. Style, dorsal view. G. Anal tube, dorsal view. No to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761694" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761694/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="84">Fig. 5G</figureCitation>
). Anal column long surpassing posterior margin of anal tube. Phallobase tubular-shaped, elongate, curved (in lateral view), apical part inflated in water after boiling (
<figureCitation box="[1070,1163,370,397]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[221,1339,427,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[189,1398,420,1852]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 5. Superciliaris anichkini sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ZIN), genitalia. A. Pygofer and anal tube, lateral view (basal part of penis showed by dotted line).B. Penis (aedeagus shaded) and connective, lateral view. C. Apical part of phallobase inflated in water. D. Penis, ventral view. E. Style, lateral view. F. Style, dorsal view. G. Anal tube, dorsal view. No to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761694" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761694/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="84">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
). Ventral phallobase lobe long and wide, slightly narrowing apically (
<figureCitation box="[750,843,406,433]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[221,1339,427,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[189,1398,420,1852]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 5. Superciliaris anichkini sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ZIN), genitalia. A. Pygofer and anal tube, lateral view (basal part of penis showed by dotted line).B. Penis (aedeagus shaded) and connective, lateral view. C. Apical part of phallobase inflated in water. D. Penis, ventral view. E. Style, lateral view. F. Style, dorsal view. G. Anal tube, dorsal view. No to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761694" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761694/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="84">Fig. 5D</figureCitation>
). Ventral aedegal hooks nearly straight, directed basally, slightly enlarged subapically, with pointed apices (
<figureCitation box="[870,997,441,468]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[221,1339,427,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[189,1398,420,1852]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 5. Superciliaris anichkini sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ZIN), genitalia. A. Pygofer and anal tube, lateral view (basal part of penis showed by dotted line).B. Penis (aedeagus shaded) and connective, lateral view. C. Apical part of phallobase inflated in water. D. Penis, ventral view. E. Style, lateral view. F. Style, dorsal view. G. Anal tube, dorsal view. No to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761694" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761694/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="84">Fig. 5B, D</figureCitation>
). Connective relatively large, with long handle. Style vertically elongate, with straight hind margin and weak comb behind neck (in lateral view) (
<figureCitation box="[276,371,511,538]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[221,1339,427,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[189,1398,420,1852]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 5. Superciliaris anichkini sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ZIN), genitalia. A. Pygofer and anal tube, lateral view (basal part of penis showed by dotted line).B. Penis (aedeagus shaded) and connective, lateral view. C. Apical part of phallobase inflated in water. D. Penis, ventral view. E. Style, lateral view. F. Style, dorsal view. G. Anal tube, dorsal view. No to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761694" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761694/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="84">Fig. 5E</figureCitation>
). Capitulum of style on distinct neck, with wide lateral tooth. Capitulum narrowing apically (in dorsal view) (
<figureCitation box="[491,581,546,573]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[221,1339,427,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[189,1398,420,1852]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 5. Superciliaris anichkini sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ZIN), genitalia. A. Pygofer and anal tube, lateral view (basal part of penis showed by dotted line).B. Penis (aedeagus shaded) and connective, lateral view. C. Apical part of phallobase inflated in water. D. Penis, ventral view. E. Style, lateral view. F. Style, dorsal view. G. Anal tube, dorsal view. No to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761694" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761694/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="84">Fig. 5F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
